commit.message: Switch from CircleCI to GitHub Actions

Bump version to 0.5.0

(I think that's a reasonable number considering the rate of changes)

Automatically decode compressed HTTP responses

Requests enables 'Accept-Encoding', but expects the adapter to
perform decoding.

Move implementation to an Adapter

This lets us actually use PyCurl with the actual Requests library.
Bump version to 0.2.2
Update CircleCI job

Pass through byte header values unmodified

Fixes: dcoles/pycurl-requests#7

Try a bit harder to guess the correct encoding

This is based off Request's `utils.get_encoding_from_headers`.

Feature request: https://github.com/dcoles/pycurl-requests/issues/6#issuecomment-1272358214
Bump version to 0.2.1

Fix incorrect header concatination in Response.headers

HTTP allows headers to be set multiple times in a response.
Clients may combine multiple header fields with the same field name into
one field by joining the header values with a comma [1].

This is the behaviour of Requests, so we mimic it.

1. https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7230#section-3.2.2

Fixes: #5

Add SetCookie test from Issue #5

According to RFC-7230 section 3.3.2, the `Set-Cookie` header is special
and does not follow the convention of using comma to seperate fields.

However, this is the behaviour of Requests, so we mimic it.

Add test for response headers

This is mainly to check that headers are correctly concatinated.

See RFC-7230 section 3.3.2 for details.

Add structures module from Requests

This is mainly used for `CaseInsensitiveDict`.

Fix test failure with recent versions of cURL

Recent versions of cURL use "Couln't" instead of "Could not".

See https://bugs.gentoo.org/777951.
Bump version to 0.2.0

commit.message: Fix CircleCI build
Bump version to 0.1.2

Remove pytest from install_requires

Fix: #4
Add CircleCI configuration

Bump Python requirement to 3.6

Python 3.5 is now end-of-life.

See https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-3510/.
Add support for HTTP Authentication

Move pytest_requests helper to tools directory

This is to prevent PyTest coverage from trying to import it.
Fix crash when urllib3 isn't installed and Timeout is unavailable
Add support for HTTP Authentication
Bump version to 0.1.1

Update README with current method of setting cURL options

When basic Session object support was implemented in
d1c8e02c6e1deacf3f32fd1216e404ac0253f1c4, it became no longer
possible to pass a `pycurl.Curl` object directly to the main API
(see #2).

The recommended way of setting cURL options is now via the `curl`
attribute on a Session object.

Closes: #2

sessions: Don't expose a `curl` parameter on the Session object

This is to match the Requests model of `Session` not taking any
paramters and options being set via attributes.
Bump version to 0.1.0
